That's why we're so proud of him. I still feel we made the best film of the year, he said. He said they were a lot more comfortable with the black chauffeur in 'Driving Miss Daisy' than with the angry characters in his film. The 1989 film, widely hailed by critics, received only two Academy Award nominations, and isn't being considered for best picture or best director. In a lecture and question-and-answer session Monday, Lee shrugged off the academy's icy treatment of his latest movie, Do the Right Thing, and blamed it on generational politics. 